🚢 Docker Cheat Sheet – Your Ultimate Guide! 🐳
💡 Docker is a must-know for developers and DevOps engineers! Whether you’re a beginner or an expert, here’s your one-stop guide for essential Docker commands! 📌

🚀 Getting Started
Check if Docker is installed and get system details:
docker --version    # Check Docker version  
docker info         # Display system info  
docker help         # Get help with commands  

📦 Image Management
Manage Docker images like a pro:
docker images                    # List all images  
docker pull <image>               # Pull an image from Docker Hub  
docker rmi <image>                # Remove an image  
docker build -t <image-name> .    # Build an image from Dockerfile  
docker tag <image> <repo>:<tag>   # Tag an image  
docker push <repo>:<tag>          # Push image to Docker Hub 

🎛️ Container Management
Run, stop, and manage containers with ease:
docker ps                         # List running containers  
docker ps -a                      # List all containers (including stopped)  
docker run <image>                # Run a new container  
docker run -d <image>             # Run in detached mode  
docker run -it <image> bash       # Start an interactive container  
docker stop <container>           # Stop a running container  
docker start <container>          # Start a stopped container  
docker restart <container>        # Restart a container  
docker rm <container>             # Remove a container  
docker logs <container>           # View logs  
docker exec -it <container> bash  # Access container shell  

🔗 Docker Networking
Connect and manage container networks:
docker network ls                 # List networks  
docker network inspect <name>      # Inspect network details  
docker network create <name>       # Create a custom network  
docker network rm <name>           # Remove a network  

💾 Docker Volumes
Manage persistent storage for containers:
docker volume ls                   # List volumes  
docker volume create <name>         # Create a volume  
docker volume rm <name>             # Remove a volume  
docker run -v <volume>:/data <image>  # Mount a volume 

🛠️ Docker Compose
Handle multi-container applications:
docker-compose up       # Start services from docker-compose.yml  
docker-compose down     # Stop services  
docker-compose ps       # List running services  
docker-compose logs     # View logs  

🔥 Dockerfile Essentials
Build custom images with these key instructions:
FROM        # Define the base image  
RUN         # Execute commands during image build  
CMD         # Default command when container starts  
ENTRYPOINT  # Main entry command with arguments  
COPY        # Copy files from host to container  
WORKDIR     # Set working directory inside the container  
EXPOSE      # Specify ports for external access  
